    "note": "Utah Code 81-6-305 (Low-Income Table, obligor's own individual income only): if the paying parent's own monthly adjusted gross income is at or below the threshold for the number of children (about $1,960 for 1 child up to $2,450 for six), the amount is looked up in this table directly using their own income -- this is the full obligation, not prorated. Above the threshold, 81-6-304's combined-income table (main schedule) applies instead, prorated by income share."
  },
  "custody_adjustment": null,
  "income_cap_behavior": "discretionary_above_cap",
  "deviation_note": "This calculator models Utah's standard sole-custody calculation (81-6-304/305) only. It does not model joint physical custody (a worksheet using each parent's overnights, Utah Code 81-6-201 et seq.) or split custody. Above $100,000/month combined adjusted gross income, Utah's tables do not extend automatically -- courts determine the amount case-by-case."
